<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tibet Invests in Agriculture, Animal Husbandry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303134994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1313 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lhasa, March 23 (XINHUA) -- The Tibet Autonomous 
Region will put more funds into its agriculture and animal 
husbandry this year, a regional government official said. 
  Agriculture and animal husbandry make up 80 percent of the 
region's local output, and this year the regional government 
will carry out a more preferential policy with regard to loans 
to the two sectors. 
  The additional funds will be used mainly to promote the 
development of farmland, grassland, hydropower stations and 
other water conservancy facilities. 
  The government will increase funding by seven million yuan 
(804,600 U.S. dollars) each year in an attempt to spread fine 
strains of crops. Chemical fertilizers will continue to be sold 
with government price support. 
  The region will also appropriate 20 million yuan each year 
to 
ensure the construction of some key or small hydropower 
stations. The funding in animal husbandry will remain at ten 
million yuan a year as before. 
  In addition to the central government's aid to impoverished 
areas, the regional government will expand the scale of loans to 
township and town enterprises to boost their growth. 

</TEXT>

