<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yunnan Border Trade Said Developing Rapidly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2403014294 Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2403014294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kunming Yunnan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yunnan's border trade has continued to develop, 
with import-export volume increasing by a wide margin. Last 
year, the province's gross import-export volume soared to 2.87 
billion yuan, up 26 percent over the previous year. 
  Yunnan boasts a border that stretches some 3,000 km, and by 
the end of 1993, 17 ports opening up to the world had been 
built. Presently, goods exported through border ports include 
steel products, building materials, electric machinery, articles 
of daily use, light industrial products, foodstuffs and 
beverages, not to mention farm and sideline produce, with the 
trade volume increasing with each passing year. Some of the 
items have become backbone products in border trade. 
  The sites for trade have changed from stalls on the streets 
to large trade cities, shopping malls, and stores. Many ports 
have built comprehensive border trade markets comprising 
transportation, telecommunications, storehouses, catering, 
hotels, and other services. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

