<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   CPPCC Vice Chairman Interviewed on 1993 Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2303074794 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 8 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> HK2303074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Wu Xueqian, vice chairman of the Chinese </F>
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National 
Committee, by unidentified RENMIN RIBAO reporter in Beijing; 
date not given: "Suiting the New Situation, Exploring a New 
Path, Making Fresh Contributions"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 7 Mar (RENMIN RIBAO)--[RENMIN RIBAO] As 
far as I know, to meet the needs of the new situation and the 
new tasks of reform, opening up, and socialist modernization, 
the Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC has energetically 
carried out fruitful explorations over the past year. Please 
tell me about the status of this effort. 
  [Wu] Faced with the constantly developing reform, opening 
up, and socialist modernization, everybody has a sense of 
urgency, and the CPPCC is no exception. How to duly give play 
to its role as an organization of the most extensive patriotic 
united front of the Chinese people and an important organ of 
multiparty cooperation under the leadership of the CPC and 
political consultation in developing the socialist market 
economy, promoting the building of socialist democracy, 
deepening reform, and safeguarding social stability is an 
important task before the CPPCC. In the past year, under the 
leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin 
as its core, the CPPCC National Committee has seriously summed 
up the past work of several CPPCC National Committees and, on 
this basis, has energetically explored a new path for the work 
of the CPPCC under the new situation. As pointed out by 
Chairman Li Ruihuan: The new situation and the new tasks have 
set new demands on the CPPCC. The new CPPCC National Committee 
should always take Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory on building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics as the guideline, should 
gain a thorough understanding of the important position and role 
of the CPPCC in the new period, should keep abreast of the new 
situation, should explore a new path, and should make new 
contributions. 
  [RENMIN RIBAO] How do you, as a vice chairman of the CPPCC, 
assess the work of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee over the 
past year? 
  [Wu] The Eighth CPPCC National Committee has made a good 
start in this first year. New progress has been made in all 
kinds of work. Many personalities at home and in the 
international community have gained a fresh understanding of the 
CPPCC, and people have begun to attach importance to and pay 
attention to the activities and role of the current CPPCC 
National Committee. All this has created favorable conditions 
for the further development of the CPPCC. It should be said 
that this is the outcome of the concerted efforts of all CPPCC 
units involved and all CPPCC members. 
  [RENMIN RIBAO] Please detail the new characteristics of the 
CPPCC's work over the past year. 
  [Wu] First of all, the understanding and activities of the 
Standing Committee in discussing and taking part in state 
affairs have been strengthened. Meetings of the CPPCC National 
Committee Standing Committee are the main form for fulfilling 
the duties of political consultation and democratic supervision 
during the adjournment of the plenary sessions and represent an 
important channel for various democratic parties, non-party 
democrats, various people's organizations, and personalities of 
various nationalities and circles to discuss and take part in 
state affairs. Over the past year, the CPPCC National Committee 
held five Standing Committee meetings for consultation and 
discussion about the economic situation of the country and the 
measures to be taken, the international situation, establishing 
the socialist market economic structure, strengthening the 
building of honest administration in state organs, punishing 
corruption, and so on. Zhu Rongji, Qian Qichen, Wen Jiabao, Wei 
Jianxing, and other leading comrades of the CPC Central 
Committee and the State Council attended the meetings, made 
reports, and took part in the consultations. With a patriotic 
heart toward the state and the people, the members of the 
Standing Committee opened their minds, frankly aired their 
views, contributed excellent measures, and put forward good 
suggestions and proposals. We seriously put these suggestions 
and proposals in order and reported to the relevant departments 
in good time. The CPC Central Committee and the State Council 
attached importance to the suggestions and proposals. 
  Second, the role of the special committees have been 
strengthened further. The CPPCC special committees are working 
organs for organizing the CPPCC members to carry out regular 
activities and are basic links for fulfilling the duties of 
political consultation and democratic supervision and for doing 
a good job in discussing and participating in state affairs. 
Over the past year, the planning, standardization, timeliness, 
and effectiveness of the work of various special committees have 
been markedly improved, and the initiative and enthusiasm of 
CPPCC members have been further brought into play. Many 
investigation reports provided by the special committees have 
produced good economic results and social benefits. 
  Third, guidance to and cooperation with local CPPCC organs 
have been strengthened to a certain extent. There are 
altogether 3,041 local CPPCC organs with 460,000 members at 
various levels. Closing ties between the CPPCC National 
Committee and the local CPPCC organs is conducive to giving play 
to the strong points of the CPPCC as a whole in jointly 
promoting the development of the CPPCC's cause. Over the past 
year, the CPPCC National Committee has attached importance to 
its ties and cooperation with local CPPCC organs. For example, 
in making study tours of various localities, main leaders of the 
CPPCC National Committee have, without exception, "visited CPPCC 
organs, met CPPCC members, and discussed matters concerning the 
CPPCC"; some special committees have held informal discussions 
on common issues in work and have carried out joint 
investigations and study on some important issues. 
  Fourth, the work of improving organs has been strengthened. 
Over the past year, we have paid attention to strengthening 
work to improve the ideology and work style of the CPPCC organs. 
Everybody has worked hard to bring about the good common 
practice of energetically making progress, stressing efficiency, 
unity, cooperation, honesty, and of being realistic. 
  [RENMIN RIBAO] Over the past year, the CPPCC National 
Committee has carried out relatively active friendly exchanges 
with foreign countries. Can you tell me something about this 
situation? 
  [Wu] The CPPCC National Committee's exchanges with foreign 
countries are an important part of China's diplomacy. In 
exchanges with foreign countries, the National Committee can 
give play to its special strength of being both "an official and 
a popular" organization. It can have high-level contacts with 
parliaments of various countries and can also establish ties 
with popular organizations. Since the First Session of the 
Eighth CPPCC National Committee, the CPPCC National Committee 
has energetically widened the scope of its exchanges with 
foreign countries and has developed activities with foreign 
countries. From the end of November to the beginning of last 
December, Chairman Li Ruihuan made an official friendly visit to 
three Southeast Asian countries and achieved complete success. 
Besides, Vice Chairmen Ye Xuanping, Seypidin Aze, Hong Xuezhi, 
Hu Sheng, Qian Weichang, Sun Fuling, and myself also visited 
some countries one after another. In the past year, the CPPCC 
National Committee has also played host to delegations from some 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

