<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Southwestern Region Cooperates in Economic Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2403122394 Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2403122394 </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seven areas and five provinces and regions 
including Sichuan, Yunnan, Guizhou, Guangxi, Tibet, Chengdu, and 
Chongqing are making concerted efforts to acquire and exploit 
markets, so that the vast southwestern region can advance with 
giant strides toward the new socialist market system. 
  The southwestern region is one of the regions in our country 
having the greatest potential for economic development. 
However, in the early 1980's its per capita gross industrial 
and agricultural production output value was 320 yuan less than 
other parts of the country. Since the establishment of 
southwestern economic cooperation in early 1984, the vast 
southwestern region has made great achievements in jointly 
acquiring and exploiting markets. In 1993, gross industrial and 
agricultural production output value of the region was more than 
230 percent higher than 10 years ago. At present, southwestern 
region has become one of the regions in China whose economic 
development is most active. 
  Over the past 10 years, the five provinces and regions and 
seven areas have removed restrictions and customs barriers, and 
opened up their markets to one another. They have cooperated in 
more than 6,000 economic projects of all kinds. In the 
transport and telecommunications field, they made joint 
investments of more than 200 million yuan to build 49 
interprovincial and interregional highways, which are 918 
kilometers in length. They have built 40 gigantic bridges or so 
in Sichuan and other places. They have opened up more than 100 
new provincial-level passenger-cargo transportation routes. 
Thanks to the support unanimously provided by various quarters, 
the projects of electrifying the Chendu-Chongqing, 
Guiyang-Kunming, and Chongqing-Guiyang railways have been 
completed ahead of time. Key postal and telecommunications 
projects, microwave communications station projects in important 
cities like Chengdu, Chongqing, Kunming and others, and the 
television satellite communication station project in Tibet have 
been brought into operation. Various parties have also made 
great progress in their joint exploitation of resources. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

