<H3> <TI>   Wu Bangguo Meets PLA Logistics Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203080894 Shanghai WEN HUI BAO in Chinese 3 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> OW2203080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanghai WEN HUI BAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Wu Bangguo and Huang Ju Meet Zhou </F>
Keyu"] 
  [Text] Lieutenant General Zhou Keyu, political commissar of 
the People's Liberation Army [PLA] General Logistics Department, 
paid a courtesy call on leading comrades of the Shanghai 
municipal party committee and government on 1 March. Wu 
Bangguo, CPC Central Committee Political Bureau member and 
secretary of the municipal party committee; Huang Ju, deputy 
secretary of the municipal party committee and mayor; and Wang 
Liping, deputy secretary, cordially met with Comrade Zhou Keyun. 
Zhou Keyu briefed the municipal leaders on his trip to Shanghai 
to oversee the change of president of the Second Military 
Medical College. Former president Major General Lu Zengqi was 
transferred to the General Logistics Department to serve as 
director of its Health Department. He was succeeded by Major 
General Wang Qingshun (3769 1987 5293), former vice president of 
the Fourth Army College. 
  Jia Yunsheng (6328 3387 5281), deputy director of the 
Political Department of the General Logistics Department; Fu 
Cuihe, political commissar of the Second Military Medical 
College; and Zhou Yupeng, secretary general of the Shanghai 
municipal party committee, attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

