<H3> <TI>   U.S. Forces Complete Withdrawal From Somalia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2503224794 Beijing XINHUA in English 2142 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2503224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, March 25 (XINHUA) -- The United States 
military forces completed their withdrawal from Somalia today, 
Defense Secretary William Perry announced here. 
  "The last C-5 aircraft left Mogadishu at 9:13 A.M. local 
time 
en route to the U.S.," Perry said at a Pentagon press briefing. 
  General Thomas Montgomery, the commander of the American 
military forces in Somalia, then departed by helicopter and he 
will be back at Andrews Air Force Base on Monday, Perry said. 
  A welcome home ceremony will be held for Thomas and about 25 
of his staff at Andrews Air Force Base on Monday. 
  "The return of General Montgomery marks the completion of 
the 
withdrawal and the exit of U.S. forces peacekeeping duties in 
Somalia," a Pentagon spokesman said. 
  About 50 American Marines were left in Somalia to guard the 
12 diplomats at the U.S. Liaison Office, and about 13 American 
military men remain at the U.N. forces' headquarters. 

</TEXT>

