<H3> <TI>   Shanghai-Based Airline To Increase Flights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603143494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1406 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 26 (XINHUA) -- The Shanghai-based 
China Eastern Airlines is to increase its flights starting from 
tomorrow on both domestic and international routes. 
  The international routes include those from Shanghai to 
Osaka 
of Japan, Los Angeles of the United States, Bangkok of Thailand, 
Singapore and Seoul of the Republic of Korea, according to the 
airport's new summer and autumn timetable. 
  Three to seven flights will be added to the Osaka route 
every 
week; two to three flights will be added to the route to Los 
Angeles, one to two flights, to Bangkok and Singapore routes, 
and three to four flights, to the routes to Fukuoka of Japan and 
Seoul every week. 
  There will be more flights both on popular domestic tourist 
routes and on short-distance routes. Five to seven flights will 
be added to the route from Shanghai to Ningbo every week, five 
to six flights, to the route to Nanchang, and eight to 15, to 
the Shanghai-Qingdao route, and 14 to 17 flights, to the 
Shanghai-Guilin route. 

</TEXT>

