<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam To Discuss DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603060794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0540 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2603060794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, China, March 26 (YONHAP) -- South Korean 
President Kim Yong-sam, winding up his visit to Japan, arrived 
here from Tokyo Saturday [26 March] to begin a five-day tour of 
China that will include talks with President Jiang Zemin. 
  Kim hopes to consult with Jiang and other Chinese leaders, 
including Prime Minister Li Peng, on the North Korean nuclear 
issue and ways to boost economic cooperation. 
  Kim will reportedly request that China, North Korea's only 
major remaining ally, exercise its influence in persuading 
Pyongyang to accept International Atomic Energy Agency 
inspections of its nuclear facilities. 
  Failing that, Kim will ask the Chinese leaders not to oppose 
any decision the United Nations Security Council makes on North 
Korea. 
  Before going to Beijing on Sunday, Kim, accompanied by his 
wife Son Myoung-sun, will visit the site of the former 
government-in-exile during the Japanese colonial days. 
  He will also tour Luxun Park in Shanghai, where Korean 
patriot Yun Pong-kil bombed Japanese dignitaries celebrating the 
birthday of their emperor, killing Gen. Yoshimori Shirakawa on 
April 29, 1932. 

</TEXT>

