<H3> <TI>   Arrives in Shanghai </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2603134894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1322 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2603134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 26 (XINHUA) -- President Kim 
Yong-sam of the Republic of Korea (ROK), as guest of Chinese 
President Jiang Zemin, arrived here this afternoon by special 
plane from Tokyo, Japan, starting his five-day official visit to 
China. 
  This is Kim's first visit to China since he assumed the ROK 
presidency. 
  Wu Jichuan, chairman of the Chinese Government reception 
committee and minister of posts and telecommunications, made a 
special trip to Shanghai on behalf of President Jiang to greet 
President Kim and his party. 
  This evening, Shanghai Mayor Huang Ju met with Kim and his 
party and hosted a banquet in their honor. 
  During the meeting, Kim said that he is glad that Shanghai, 
China's largest economic center, is the first leg of his China 
visit. 
  Kim said that with the establishment of diplomatic ties 
between the ROK and China more than one years ago, bilateral 
cooperation in various fields has been further enhanced, adding 
that bilateral trade volume last year was over 10 billion U.S. 
dollars, which is predicated to be further increased this year. 
  The ROK president expressed his belief that Shanghai will 
play a bigger role in its economic exchanges with the ROK. 
  This afternoon, right after their arrival here, Kim and his 
party visited the site of the former provisional government of 
the ROK. 

</TEXT>

