<H3> <TI>   Attend Signing of Agreements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2803075294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0728 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2803075294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 28 (XINHUA) -- Two agreements 
between the governments of China and the Republic of Korea (ROK) 
were signed here today. 
  They are an agreement on cultural cooperation, and another 
on 
the avoidance of double income taxation and the prevention of 
tax evasion, the 36th of its kind between China and foreign 
countries. 
  According to the cultural agreement, the two countries will 
strengthen and promote exchanges and cooperation in the fields 
of education, science, culture and art, the press, broadcasting, 
film, television, publishing and youth activities as well as 
sports. 
  Chinese President Jiang Zemin and visiting ROK President Kim 
Yong-sam were present at the signing ceremony. 

</TEXT>

