<H3> <TI>   North Korea `Will Not Yield' To Pressure From U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2703220894 Beijing XINHUA in English 2154 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2703220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Luanda, March 27 (XINHUA) -- Pak Myong-ku, deputy 
foreign minister of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, 
said here today that his country will not yield to the pressure 
from the United States. 
  Pak Myong-ku said this on his arrival at the Luanda 
International Airport. He has come here to pay a five-day visit 
to Angola. 
  If the United States exerts pressure on his country by force 
of arms, North Korea will "take appropriate steps," he said. 
  He said, "We are ready politically and militarily to deal 
with the United States on our own, and the Americans should know 
this." 
  Pak Myong-ku said his visit to the southern African country 
will "promote the bilateral relations between the two countries." 

</TEXT>

